The paper deals with designing robust policies for controlling a mecanum-wheeled robot, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep neural networks for policy design and the proposed minimax iterative dynamic game framework suggest that the paper also belongs to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on robustness against disturbances, model mismatch, or model uncertainties indicates that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of control systems (cs.SY) and neural networks (cs.NE).
